back into balance with nature

00:00:32.590 --> 00:00:34.780 align:middle line:10%
by living in sync with
its circadian rhythms,

00:00:34.780 --> 00:00:38.500 align:middle line:10%
restoring digestive and,
particularly, lymphatic health.

00:00:38.500 --> 00:00:41.770 align:middle line:84%
This allows the body and
mind to access a deeper state

00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:43.660 align:middle line:90%
of self-awareness and healing.

00:00:43.660 --> 00:00:45.910 align:middle line:84%
With us today is
Dr. John Douillard.

00:00:45.910 --> 00:00:48.940 align:middle line:84%
He is a bestselling author,
a globally-recognized leader

00:00:48.940 --> 00:00:52.690 align:middle line:84%
in the fields of natural health,
Ayurveda, and sports medicine.

00:00:52.690 --> 00:00:55.420 align:middle line:84%
His website,
lifespa.com, is evolving

00:00:55.420 --> 00:00:58.870 align:middle line:84%
the way Ayurveda is
understood around the world,

00:00:58.870 --> 00:01:02.080 align:middle line:84%
with over 9 million
YouTube views.

00:01:02.080 --> 00:01:02.950 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, Dr. John.

00:01:02.950 --> 00:01:04.892 align:middle line:90%
It's so wonderful to have you.

00:01:04.892 --> 00:01:06.350 align:middle line:84%
>>JOHN DOUILLARD:
Great to be here.

00:01:06.350 --> 00:01:08.690 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: I also have to say,
you're a friend of mine.

00:01:08.690 --> 00:01:09.970 align:middle line:90%
And it's so good to see you.

00:01:09.970 --> 00:01:11.410 align:middle line:90%
I haven't seen you in 15 years.

00:01:11.410 --> 00:01:13.980 align:middle line:84%
And I'm thrilled to be involved
in the conversation today.

00:01:13.980 --> 00:01:14.980 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Absolutely.

00:01:14.980 --> 00:01:16.022 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: I look so forward.

00:01:16.022 --> 00:01:18.460 align:middle line:84%
So, OK, let's start
from the beginning.

00:01:18.460 --> 00:01:20.720 align:middle line:84%
You went to India
a long time ago.

00:01:20.720 --> 00:01:22.330 align:middle line:84%
And you went for
a three week trip.

00:01:22.330 --> 00:01:24.620 align:middle line:84%
And you stayed for
a year and a half.

00:01:24.620 --> 00:01:25.420 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:01:25.420 --> 00:01:26.220 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Yeah.

00:01:26.220 --> 00:01:28.500 align:middle line:10%
You know, the
quick, long story--

00:01:28.500 --> 00:01:32.470 align:middle line:10%
I was scheduled to ride
mountain bikes from Lhasa, Tibet

00:01:32.470 --> 00:01:33.580 align:middle line:10%
to Kathmandu.

00:01:33.580 --> 00:01:35.410 align:middle line:10%
And the Chinese government
gave this window

00:01:35.410 --> 00:01:37.670 align:middle line:10%
of where you could do that.

00:01:37.670 --> 00:01:40.300 align:middle line:84%
My brother-in-law,
who is Doug Henning--

00:01:40.300 --> 00:01:42.130 align:middle line:84%
the magician from
way back when--

00:01:42.130 --> 00:01:43.735 align:middle line:84%
had a dream, vision,
a lucid dream,

00:01:43.735 --> 00:01:44.860 align:middle line:90%
that there was an accident.

00:01:44.860 --> 00:01:46.793 align:middle line:84%
And I was paralyzed
from the waist down.

00:01:46.793 --> 00:01:48.460 align:middle line:84%
And I was playing
wheelchair basketball.

00:01:48.460 --> 00:01:51.130 align:middle line:84%
And he said, please don't
go I was like, really?

00:01:51.130 --> 00:01:53.650 align:middle line:90%
You can't do that to me.

00:01:53.650 --> 00:01:58.240 align:middle line:84%
My mother had a similar dream
and said, please don't go.

00:01:58.240 --> 00:01:59.200 align:middle line:90%
So I didn't go.

00:01:59.200 --> 00:02:00.860 align:middle line:90%
But I had all this time.

00:02:00.860 --> 00:02:03.520 align:middle line:84%
So I went to India to try
to study Ayurvedic medicine.

00:02:03.520 --> 00:02:05.725 align:middle line:84%
I went for a three
week vacation,

00:02:05.725 --> 00:02:07.480 align:middle line:84%
and ended up finding
a teacher there

00:02:07.480 --> 00:02:08.830 align:middle line:90%
who was willing to teach me.

00:02:08.830 --> 00:02:11.120 align:middle line:84%
And I stayed there
for a year and a half.

00:02:11.120 --> 00:02:13.930 align:middle line:84%
And when I came back,
somebody I didn't even know

00:02:13.930 --> 00:02:14.830 align:middle line:90%
was driving my car.

00:02:14.830 --> 00:02:16.750 align:middle line:84%
My stuff was in about
five different homes.

00:02:16.750 --> 00:02:18.340 align:middle line:84%
And I kind of put
it all together

00:02:18.340 --> 00:02:20.660 align:middle line:90%
and started my life again.

00:02:20.660 --> 00:02:22.530 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So you
literally just stayed?

00:02:22.530 --> 00:02:23.370 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: I
literally just stayed.

00:02:23.370 --> 00:02:24.350 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Just like,
I'm not coming back.

00:02:24.350 --> 00:02:25.130 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: I didn't come back.

00:02:25.130 --> 00:02:25.690 align:middle line:90%
I had a practice.

00:02:25.690 --> 00:02:27.610 align:middle line:84%
I called my partner and I
said, I'm not coming back.

00:02:27.610 --> 00:02:29.170 align:middle line:84%
And back then, it
took like an hour

00:02:29.170 --> 00:02:31.120 align:middle line:90%
to get a line to call America.

00:02:31.120 --> 00:02:32.320 align:middle line:90%
And he could barely hear me.

00:02:32.320 --> 00:02:34.640 align:middle line:84%
And all he really got
was, I'm not coming back.

00:02:34.640 --> 00:02:35.440 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yeah.

00:02:35.440 --> 00:02:36.310 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: And that was it.

00:02:36.310 --> 00:02:37.810 align:middle line:84%
And I just said,
you know, it's just

00:02:37.810 --> 00:02:40.390 align:middle line:84%
kind of one of those things
where I just said, yes.

00:02:40.390 --> 00:02:41.590 align:middle line:90%
I'm doing this.

00:02:41.590 --> 00:02:43.900 align:middle line:84%
I had student loans
and a lot of reasons

00:02:43.900 --> 00:02:46.840 align:middle line:84%
why I shouldn't have
done that, but I just

00:02:46.840 --> 00:02:49.560 align:middle line:84%
knew that this was an
opportunity of a lifetime.

00:02:49.560 --> 00:02:51.912 align:middle line:90%
And what was really weird--

00:02:51.912 --> 00:02:53.620 align:middle line:84%
and I stayed there
for a year and a half,

00:02:53.620 --> 00:02:56.830 align:middle line:84%
studied Ayurvedic medicine,
met Deepak Chopra there,

00:02:56.830 --> 00:02:58.630 align:middle line:84%
came back and ran a
center for eight years,

00:02:58.630 --> 00:02:59.920 align:middle line:90%
taught medical doctors.

00:02:59.920 --> 00:03:01.400 align:middle line:84%
But I never-- when
I was in India

00:03:01.400 --> 00:03:03.820 align:middle line:84%
for that year and a half--
never, for one minute,

00:03:03.820 --> 00:03:05.410 align:middle line:84%
did I ever think
that I would actually

00:03:05.410 --> 00:03:09.310 align:middle line:84%
use Ayurvedic knowledge in
my life or in my practice.

00:03:09.310 --> 00:03:10.570 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't like, oh, great.

00:03:10.570 --> 00:03:12.945 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to get this knowledge
and come back and then do

00:03:12.945 --> 00:03:14.190 align:middle line:90%
Ayurvedic medicine.

00:03:14.190 --> 00:03:16.060 align:middle line:84%
I think I just think
too slow for that.

00:03:16.060 --> 00:03:18.620 align:middle line:84%
I was just, like, so
wrapped up in the experience

00:03:18.620 --> 00:03:19.420 align:middle line:90%
of the moment.

00:03:19.420 --> 00:03:23.150 align:middle line:84%
It was so juicy that I
just went like, I'm in.

00:03:23.150 --> 00:03:24.858 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know
where this is going.

00:03:24.858 --> 00:03:25.900 align:middle line:90%
But I didn't have a plan.

00:03:25.900 --> 00:03:27.275 align:middle line:84%
I think that was
the magic of it.

00:03:27.275 --> 00:03:29.330 align:middle line:84%
I was just so locked
into the present moment.

00:03:29.330 --> 00:03:31.180 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So I think
that that's really

00:03:31.180 --> 00:03:33.320 align:middle line:90%
how authentic paths unfold.

00:03:33.320 --> 00:03:34.360 align:middle line:90%
It's one step at a time.

00:03:34.360 --> 00:03:35.978 align:middle line:90%
We're drawn into it.

00:03:35.978 --> 00:03:38.020 align:middle line:84%
It's almost like the
universe conspires to put us

00:03:38.020 --> 00:03:40.550 align:middle line:84%
in our true expression
in the world.

00:03:40.550 --> 00:03:43.533 align:middle line:84%
And that is definitely what I
have watched happen with you.

00:03:43.533 --> 00:03:44.950 align:middle line:84%
So tell us a little
bit about what

00:03:44.950 --> 00:03:46.540 align:middle line:90%
it was like meeting Deepak.

00:03:46.540 --> 00:03:48.730 align:middle line:84%
Of course, we want to dive
into that a little bit.

00:03:48.730 --> 00:03:52.390 align:middle line:84%
People love to hear about how
wonderful people work together,

00:03:52.390 --> 00:03:54.565 align:middle line:84%
find each other, and
produce amazing things.

00:03:54.565 --> 00:03:55.690 align:middle line:90%
What can you share with us?

00:03:55.690 --> 00:03:58.690 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: I met him in the
Oberoi Hotel in New Delhi.

00:03:58.690 --> 00:04:04.090 align:middle line:84%
And he was working in India
with Maharishi, the founder

00:04:04.090 --> 00:04:05.360 align:middle line:90%
of the TM Organization.

00:04:05.360 --> 00:04:07.150 align:middle line:84%
And that was the hub
that I had as well,

00:04:07.150 --> 00:04:09.790 align:middle line:84%
because my sister
was really into that.

00:04:09.790 --> 00:04:12.620 align:middle line:84%
And it's hard to go
into all the details,

00:04:12.620 --> 00:04:15.940 align:middle line:84%
but I ended up meeting my wife
from Santa Barbara in India.

00:04:15.940 --> 00:04:18.279 align:middle line:84%
And we went back, got
married real quick,

00:04:18.279 --> 00:04:19.820 align:middle line:90%
and came back to India.

00:04:19.820 --> 00:04:23.030 align:middle line:84%
And she was pregnant now,
fainting in the streets

00:04:23.030 --> 00:04:23.830 align:middle line:90%
of New Delhi.

00:04:23.830 --> 00:04:26.680 align:middle line:84%
And it became clear we
had to get out of India

00:04:26.680 --> 00:04:27.700 align:middle line:90%
and have this baby.

00:04:27.700 --> 00:04:29.200 align:middle line:84%
And Deepak said,
well, you know, I'm

00:04:29.200 --> 00:04:31.520 align:middle line:84%
having the opening of the
center in Massachusetts.

00:04:31.520 --> 00:04:32.320 align:middle line:90%
You can come back.

00:04:32.320 --> 00:04:33.820 align:middle line:84%
You can co-direct it
with me, because I had

00:04:33.820 --> 00:04:34.987 align:middle line:90%
all this Ayurvedic training.

00:04:34.987 --> 00:04:36.910 align:middle line:84%
And there wasn't a
lot of people who

00:04:36.910 --> 00:04:39.620 align:middle line:84%
had a lot of Ayurvedic training
in the west at that point.

00:04:39.620 --> 00:04:40.730 align:middle line:90%
And so I did.

00:04:40.730 --> 00:04:42.700 align:middle line:90%
I came back and ran his center.

00:04:42.700 --> 00:04:46.137 align:middle line:84%
And we actually shared the
same desk for eight years.

00:04:46.137 --> 00:04:48.220 align:middle line:84%
He'd come two times a week,
I'd come three times--

00:04:48.220 --> 00:04:50.990 align:middle line:84%
two, three times a week-- and
became really good friends.

00:04:50.990 --> 00:04:53.290 align:middle line:84%
And you know, I have nothing
but the highest respect

00:04:53.290 --> 00:04:54.540 align:middle line:90%
from his knowledge and wisdom.

00:04:54.540 --> 00:04:57.610 align:middle line:84%
I got to watch him grow
from being a medical doctor,

00:04:57.610 --> 00:04:59.140 align:middle line:90%
to being Deepak Chopra.

00:04:59.140 --> 00:05:01.030 align:middle line:84%
And it was an amazing
thing to watch.

00:05:01.030 --> 00:05:05.350 align:middle line:84%
I learned a lot from him
about so many things,

00:05:05.350 --> 00:05:08.320 align:middle line:84%
and how I wanted
to position myself

00:05:08.320 --> 00:05:09.590 align:middle line:90%
in my life and my career.

00:05:09.590 --> 00:05:10.390 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Right.

00:05:10.390 --> 00:05:13.240 align:middle line:84%
And at that time, then,
you went into more

00:05:13.240 --> 00:05:14.230 align:middle line:90%
of a private practice.

00:05:14.230 --> 00:05:19.030 align:middle line:84%
And you started expressing
your gifts and your desire

00:05:19.030 --> 00:05:21.400 align:middle line:84%
to serve humanity
through Ayurveda.

00:05:21.400 --> 00:05:23.673 align:middle line:84%
Can you share a little
bit about what Ayurveda

00:05:23.673 --> 00:05:26.090 align:middle line:84%
is for our viewers, and just
get everyone on the same page

00:05:26.090 --> 00:05:26.500 align:middle line:90%
there?

00:05:26.500 --> 00:05:26.650 align:middle line:90%
>>DOUILLARD: Yeah.

00:05:26.650 --> 00:05:28.570 align:middle line:84%
So Deepak-- when I
travelled with Deepak,

00:05:28.570 --> 00:05:30.670 align:middle line:84%
and we lectured for eight
years together as well.

00:05:30.670 --> 00:05:32.800 align:middle line:84%
And he was like
the wow of people.

00:05:32.800 --> 00:05:35.133 align:middle line:84%
And I was the guy that would
come in after and then give

00:05:35.133 --> 00:05:37.320 align:middle line:84%
them the nuts and bolts of
how to eat, how to sleep,

00:05:37.320 --> 00:05:38.440 align:middle line:90%
when to eat, what to eat--

00:05:38.440 --> 00:05:41.360 align:middle line:84%
all the details of how to
live a healthy, healthy life.

00:05:41.360 --> 00:05:45.790 align:middle line:84%
And that's been sort of
my world over the years,

00:05:45.790 --> 00:05:48.550 align:middle line:84%
is working more one-on-one
and diving really deep

00:05:48.550 --> 00:05:52.720 align:middle line:84%
into Ayurvedic health,
Ayurvedic psychology--

00:05:52.720 --> 00:05:55.480 align:middle line:84%
and really understanding
how to help guide people

00:05:55.480 --> 00:05:57.600 align:middle line:90%
on their journey to wellness.

00:05:57.600 --> 00:05:58.620 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Excellent.

00:05:58.620 --> 00:06:01.840 align:middle line:84%
And so tell us a little
bit about the foundation

00:06:01.840 --> 00:06:04.810 align:middle line:84%
of Ayurveda-- the structure,
what it is as an approach

00:06:04.810 --> 00:06:05.940 align:middle line:90%
to wellness--

00:06:05.940 --> 00:06:07.857 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: There's two
definitions of Ayur--

00:06:07.857 --> 00:06:09.580 align:middle line:84%
Ayu means "life", Veda
means "knowledge".

00:06:09.580 --> 00:06:12.093 align:middle line:84%
And you can think of Ayurveda
as the science of life--

00:06:12.093 --> 00:06:13.510 align:middle line:84%
how to live in
sync and in harmony

00:06:13.510 --> 00:06:15.923 align:middle line:84%
with the cycles of nature,
how to go downstream

00:06:15.923 --> 00:06:18.340 align:middle line:84%
with the current versus swimming
against the grain, right?

00:06:18.340 --> 00:06:20.410 align:middle line:84%
We all feel that
against-the-grain feeling.

00:06:20.410 --> 00:06:22.010 align:middle line:84%
You're exhausted at
the end of the day

00:06:22.010 --> 00:06:25.730 align:middle line:84%
and, you know, recovering on
the weekend, stuff like that.

00:06:25.730 --> 00:06:27.610 align:middle line:84%
But then there's
the real definition

00:06:27.610 --> 00:06:31.150 align:middle line:84%
of Ayurveda, which is sort
of the Vedic definition--

00:06:31.150 --> 00:06:33.910 align:middle line:84%
Veda meaning "truth",
Ayu meaning "life".

00:06:33.910 --> 00:06:38.960 align:middle line:84%
It's about a science to
unfold the truth of your life.

00:06:38.960 --> 00:06:41.320 align:middle line:84%
How do you let who
you truly are out?

00:06:41.320 --> 00:06:44.440 align:middle line:84%
Because we all sort of know that
it's this crazy mind of ours

00:06:44.440 --> 00:06:48.260 align:middle line:84%
that impacts us in ways
that take us out mentally,

00:06:48.260 --> 00:06:49.330 align:middle line:90%
physically, emotionally.

00:06:49.330 --> 00:06:52.300 align:middle line:84%
Most of our health concerns
come from how we handle

00:06:52.300 --> 00:06:54.070 align:middle line:90%
or don't handle stress, right?

00:06:54.070 --> 00:06:56.340 align:middle line:84%
So understanding that
component is huge.

00:06:56.340 --> 00:07:01.060 align:middle line:84%
So how do we let
the truth of us out?

00:07:01.060 --> 00:07:04.415 align:middle line:84%
How do we let go of old
protective patterns of behavior

00:07:04.415 --> 00:07:06.790 align:middle line:84%
we created as young children,
that we're still protecting

00:07:06.790 --> 00:07:08.320 align:middle line:90%
on the screen today as adults?

00:07:08.320 --> 00:07:10.270 align:middle line:90%
How do we unravel all that?

00:07:10.270 --> 00:07:13.030 align:middle line:84%
How do we become conscious
and free ourselves

00:07:13.030 --> 00:07:14.590 align:middle line:84%
from these patterns
that are based

00:07:14.590 --> 00:07:17.370 align:middle line:84%
on needing to be loved and
approved of and appreciated

00:07:17.370 --> 00:07:18.380 align:middle line:90%
by everybody else?

00:07:18.380 --> 00:07:20.690 align:middle line:84%
And how do we get
ourselves to be that love?

00:07:20.690 --> 00:07:21.880 align:middle line:90%
It's a little risky.

00:07:21.880 --> 00:07:24.400 align:middle line:84%
How do you let the delicate
petals of your flower open,

00:07:24.400 --> 00:07:27.220 align:middle line:84%
and let something delicate
and vulnerable-- yet,

00:07:27.220 --> 00:07:28.450 align:middle line:90%
the most powerful part us--

00:07:28.450 --> 00:07:28.950 align:middle line:90%
out?

00:07:28.950 --> 00:07:29.800 align:middle line:90%
That's Ayurveda.

00:07:29.800 --> 00:07:30.600 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Right.

00:07:30.600 --> 00:07:33.310 align:middle line:84%
And so a lot of people
have it that Ayurveda

00:07:33.310 --> 00:07:37.000 align:middle line:84%
is kind of compartmentalized
into these doshas.

00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:41.020 align:middle line:84%
And working with the doshas
gets you a start in a doorway

00:07:41.020 --> 00:07:42.670 align:middle line:84%
into starting to
understand this.

00:07:42.670 --> 00:07:44.020 align:middle line:90%
Can you just speak a little bit?

00:07:44.020 --> 00:07:46.900 align:middle line:84%
I know that you have
your own understanding

00:07:46.900 --> 00:07:49.830 align:middle line:90%
about the perspective there.

00:07:49.830 --> 00:07:52.630 align:middle line:84%
>>DOUILLARD: I think that the
doshas are really important.

00:07:52.630 --> 00:07:54.790 align:middle line:84%
They are the aspects of
nature, the governing

00:07:54.790 --> 00:07:55.840 align:middle line:90%
principles of nature.

00:07:55.840 --> 00:07:57.040 align:middle line:90%
Winter is Vata.

00:07:57.040 --> 00:07:59.140 align:middle line:84%
It's cold and dry and
moving all the time.

00:07:59.140 --> 00:08:01.750 align:middle line:84%
And people with a lot of
Vata, they're cold and dry.

00:08:01.750 --> 00:08:03.495 align:middle line:84%
And they need more
blankets, you know?

00:08:03.495 --> 00:08:04.870 align:middle line:84%
And their nervous
system is going

00:08:04.870 --> 00:08:06.940 align:middle line:84%
